216A 101st Legislative Session 216
2026 South Dakota Legislature
Senate Bill 216
AMENDME NT 216A
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Senator Hulse
This bill has been extensively amended (hoghoused) and may no longer be consistent with the original
intention of the sponsor.
1 An Act to limit annual valuation increases on owner-occupied single-family
2 dwellings and provide an exception for mill rate limitations on taxing
3 districtsprovide a use for moneys deposited into the homeowner tax
4 reduction fund.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
6 Section 1. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 10-13:
7 The moneys in the homeowner tax reduction fund, as created in Senate Bill 125,
8 and enacted by the One Hundred First Legislature, must be used to reduce the maximum
9 mill levies imposed on owner-occupied single-family dwellings for school district general
10 fund and special education fund levies.
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

